{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"FeaturePolicy: allowsFeature() method","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy/allowsFeature","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","browserCompat":["api.FeaturePolicy.allowsFeature"],"sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy\"><code>FeaturePolicy</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Instance methods</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy/allowedFeatures\"><code>allowedFeatures()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><em><code>allowsFeature()</code> <abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy/features\"><code>features()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy/getAllowlistForFeature\"><code>getAllowlistForFeature()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"APIRef","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard experimental\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Experimental:</strong> <strong>This is an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Writing_guidelines/Experimental_deprecated_obsolete#experimental\">experimental technology</a></strong><br>Check the <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">Browser compatibility table</a> carefully before using this in production.</p></div>\n<p>\n  The <strong><code>allowsFeature()</code></strong> method of\n  the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy\"><code>FeaturePolicy</code></a> interface enables introspection of individual\n  directives of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Permissions_Policy\">Permissions Policy</a> it is run on. It returns a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean\"><code>Boolean</code></a>\n  that is <code>true</code> if and only if the specified feature is allowed in the\n  specified context (or the default context if no context is specified).\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> allowed <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> FeaturePolicy<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">allowsFeature</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>feature<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>or</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> allowed <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> FeaturePolicy<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">allowsFeature</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>feature<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> origin<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<h4 id=\"feature_name\"><code>Feature name</code></h4>\n<p>A specific feature name must be specified.</p>\n<h4 id=\"origin_name_optional\"><code>Origin name</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></h4>\n<p>An origin URL to check the feature on. If it is omitted the default origin is used.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean\"><code>Boolean</code></a> that is <code>true</code> if and only if the feature is\n  allowed.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example","title":"Example","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The following example queries whether or not the document is allowed to use camera API\n  by the Permissions Policy. Please note that Camera API might be restricted by the\n  Permissions API, if the user did not grant the corresponding permission yet.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">// First, get the Feature Policy object</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> featurePolicy <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>featurePolicy<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Then query feature for specific</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> allowed <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> featurePolicy<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">allowsFeature</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"camera\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>allowed<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"FP allows camera.\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"FP does not allows camera.\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[],"query":"api.FeaturePolicy.allowsFeature"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.FeaturePolicy.allowsFeature"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Example","id":"example"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The allowsFeature() method of\n  the FeaturePolicy interface enables introspection of individual\n  directives of the Permissions Policy it is run on. It returns a Boolean\n  that is true if and only if the specified feature is allowed in the\n  specified context (or the default context if no context is specified).","popularity":0,"modified":"2023-04-07T05:59:30.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/featurepolicy/allowsfeature","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/featurepolicy/allowsfeature/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/339595951b78774e951b1a9d215a6db6b856f6b2","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"allowsFeature()","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy","title":"FeaturePolicy"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FeaturePolicy/allowsFeature","title":"allowsFeature()"}],"pageTitle":"FeaturePolicy: allowsFeature() method - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}